---
import ConditionPage from '../../components/ConditionPage.astro';
---
<ConditionPage
	title="Treatment in Clapham"
	highlight="Parkinson's"
	heroSubtitle="Parkinson's varies greatly between people — but the right approach can make a meaningful difference to how you move and feel day to day."
	breadcrumb="Parkinson's"
	seoTitle="Parkinson's Treatment in Clapham"
	seoDescription="Specialist Parkinson's physiotherapy in Clapham, London. Evidence-based neurological rehab to improve mobility, balance and confidence day to day."
	intro={[
		"Parkinson's is a progressive neurological condition which varies greatly among individuals — but the right approach can make a meaningful difference to how you move and feel day to day.",
		"We provide targeted, evidence-based rehabilitation, combining hands-on support with movement strategies to help you maintain mobility, independence, and confidence for as long as possible.",
	]}
	symptomsHeading="When to get"
	symptomsHighlight="support"
	symptomsIntro="Physiotherapy can help if you're experiencing any of the following:"
	symptomsList={[
		"Slower or smaller movements (bradykinesia)",
		"Stiffness in the limbs or trunk",
		"Tremor affecting daily tasks",
		"Difficulty starting and stopping movement",
		"Balance issues or fear of falling",
		"Changes in walking, such as shuffling or reduced arm swing",
		"Freezing episodes where your feet feel stuck",
	]}
	treatmentHeading="How we treat"
	treatmentHighlight="Parkinson's"
	treatmentIntro="Your plan is shaped around your symptoms and goals, and may include:"
	treatmentList={[
		"Physiotherapy to improve mobility, coordination and strength",
		"Gait training to improve walking and reduce movement initiation difficulties",
		"Large-amplitude (\"BIG\") movement training",
		"Balance and falls prevention work",
		"Strength and conditioning to maintain physical capacity",
		"Advice on daily movement strategies and routines",
	]}
	whoHeading="Who we"
	whoHighlight="help"
	whoList={[
		"Newly diagnosed individuals looking to stay ahead of symptoms",
		"People managing early to mid-stage Parkinson's",
		"Those experiencing difficulty initiating movement or changes in walking",
		"Individuals with reduced balance or increased fall risk",
		"Family members and carers needing guidance and support",
	]}
	faqs={[
		{ q: "Can physiotherapy help with Parkinson's?", a: "Yes — targeted exercise and movement training can improve mobility, balance and overall function." },
		{ q: "What is freezing of gait?", a: "It\\'s when movement temporarily stops, often during walking or turning. We can teach strategies to help overcome it." },
		{ q: "Should I keep exercising?", a: "Yes — staying active is one of the most important parts of managing Parkinson\\'s. We\\'ll guide you safely." },
		{ q: "Do you provide exercises to do at home?", a: "Absolutely. A structured home programme is key to maintaining progress between sessions." },
		{ q: "Can you help with balance and falls?", a: "Yes — we focus on improving balance, strength and confidence to reduce fall risk." },
	]}
/>
